title: For Sale:  Ruger SP101 .357 magnum Wiley Clapp special edition - Like new in box
postcontent:
For sale here is my Ruger SP101, 2" barrel .357 magnum.  Selling to buy my wife a 9mm pistol
This is the "Wiley Clapp" special edition, model number KSP-321X-NVK.  It's a Talo distributor exclusive model.  Differences between this and a standard SP101:
--- Really nice Novak dovetailed sights, which can be drifted to adjust.
--- The front sight has a bright brass bead.  The sight picture is easy to see compared to a standard SP.
--- The top strap of the gun is a solid slab of steel, not machined out for a sight groove like the regular SP.
--- The cylinder is tapered for easy holstering.
--- The grips have a nice wood inlay.--- The action and external surfaces are more nicely polished by Ruger.  No sharp edges along the trigger guard, etc. like on a standard SP101.
You can read a good review of the Wiley Clapp model here:  http://www.luckygunner.com/lounge/ruger-sp-101-the-shooters-snub-nose/
I have only put 150 rounds through this gun and it's truly a perfect specimen.  I mean, this is like an heirloom-quality gun.  The nicest SP101 I've ever seen or handled.  The barrel/cylinder gap is the tightest I've seen on a revolver made in the last few decades, but it doesn't drag on the barrel; my feeler gauges show a .003-.004" gap.  The cylinder locks up totally tight with no shake at all, and the trigger is very, very smooth.  I have lightened it up further with a Wolff 10-pound hammer spring, and the full Wolff spring set is included with the gun, along with the stock 16-pound factory spring.
The 150 rounds I put through it showed it to be exceptionally accurate with .357 or .38 special.  From a sandbag rested position I was shooting <3” groups at 25 yards, but most of that variation was probably my lack of skills.
Gun comes with everything still in the box right down to the little yellow protective disk and all the plastic and manuals.  Also included is a nice, leather OWB holster and the Wolff spring kit.
Price is $600 cash, firm.  No trades.  Pick-up at my place in Southwest Lincoln most evenings and weekends.  Buyer will need to show everything required by law: valid NE purchase permit and ID, or NE CHP permit.
Please reply via Armslist message with your preferred contact info.
